Privacy Policy

Effective Date: February 3, 2026
Business Name: StocksCommunity
Owner: Sam Putnam, Sole Proprietor
Address: 4049 Brownsville Hartland Rd, West Windsor, VT 05089
Email: sam@samputnam.com

Website: stockscommunity.com

1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how Sam Putnam, doing business as StocksCommunity (“StocksCommunity,” “we,” “us,” or “our”), collects, uses, shares, and protects your information when you visit stockscommunity.com, subscribe to our services, or otherwise interact with us.

By using our website, subscribing to our monthly service, or entering your email or phone number anywhere on stockscommunity.com, you consent to the practices described in this Policy.

2. Information We Collect

We collect information directly from you when you:

Sign up for the monthly service or trial period;

Subscribe to our newsletter or community updates;

Enter your information for a promotion, offer, or partner opportunity;

Contact us for support or customer service.

The types of information we collect may include:

Contact Information: your name, email address, and phone number;

Billing Information: payment details such as card type, expiration date, and billing address (processed securely by our payment provider);

Usage Information: how you interact with our website, emails, and SMS messages;

Voluntary Submissions: messages or content you share in the community or when you contact us directly.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from individuals under 18 years old.

3. How We Use Your Information

We use your information to:

Provide and manage your monthly subscription service;

Process your payments and send billing reminders;

Send educational materials, newsletters, and updates;

Deliver SMS and email communications, including partner offers and promotions;

Improve and personalize our content and user experience;

Respond to customer inquiries or support requests; and

Comply with applicable laws and regulations.

We may use anonymized, aggregated data to analyze service performance and usage trends.

4. Partner Offers and Communications

By entering your email address or phone number on stockscommunity.com, you consent to receive:

Emails and SMS messages from StocksCommunity or Sam Putnam;

Partner offers, promotions, and sponsored content related to stock market education or related opportunities.

You can unsubscribe from email messages at any time by using the “unsubscribe” link included in each email.

SMS messages are managed separately — you can unsubscribe from SMS messages at any time by replying STOP, END, CANCEL, UNSUBSCRIBE, or QUIT.

Unsubscribing from one list does not automatically remove you from the other.

We are not responsible for the accuracy or claims made in partner messages. Those offers are provided for informational purposes only.

5. How We Share Information

We may share limited information in the following circumstances:

Service Providers: with trusted third parties that help us deliver our Services (e.g., payment processors, email and SMS delivery platforms, or web hosting providers);

Legal Requirements: when required to comply with applicable law, regulation, or legal process;

Business Transfers: if we ever transfer or sell part of the business (e.g., in a merger or sale of assets);

With Your Consent: when you expressly authorize us to share your information with another party.

We do not sell your personal information.

6. Payment Processing and Security

All payments for StocksCommunity’s monthly subscription or trial periods are securely processed through third-party payment processors. We do not directly store your full payment details.

We use commercially reasonable safeguards — including encryption and access controls — to protect your personal information. However, no internet-based service is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security of your data.

7. Data Retention

We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to provide our Services, comply with legal obligations, or resolve disputes.

You may request deletion of your personal data by emailing sam@samputnam.com
, though we may retain certain records as required by law or for legitimate business purposes (such as transaction records).

8. Your Choices and Rights

You may:

Access or correct your personal information by contacting sam@samputnam.com
;

Unsubscribe from marketing emails at any time;

Stop receiving SMS messages by following the opt-out instructions in any message;

Cancel your monthly subscription at any time (future months only; no refunds for prior payments).

If you are located in a jurisdiction that provides additional privacy rights (such as California or the European Union), you may have rights to request access, deletion, or restriction of processing of your personal data. Such requests can be sent to sam@samputnam.com
.

9. Cookies and Tracking

We use cookies and similar technologies to improve website performance, analyze usage, and personalize content.

You can disable cookies in your browser settings, but this may affect your experience on our website.

10. Third-Party Links

StocksCommunity may include links or promotions from third-party partners. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of those websites. Please review their privacy policies before sharing personal information with them.

11. Children’s Privacy

Our Services are not directed to anyone under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from minors. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us immediately at sam@samputnam.com
 so we can delete it.

12. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be posted on stockscommunity.com with an updated “Effective Date.” Continued use of our website or Services after an update means you accept the revised Policy.

13. Contact Information

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how your information is handled, please contact:

